10/09/2003
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- Foreign Minister Solomon Passy and his Iranian counterpart, Kamal Kharazi, met on Tuesday (9 September) to discuss economic ties and bilateral co-operation. They also discussed the problem of drug trafficking via Bulgarian and Iranian routes to Western Europe.
In other news Tuesday, Deputy Foreign Minister Lyubomir Ivanov said that the United States has agreed to provide assistance in controlling the trade and export of Bulgarian weapons.
Meanwhile, Bulgarian custom officers seized their third large heroin haul in four days. The officers found 6kg of heroin in a truck crossing Bulgaria en route from Turkey to Romania. (Trud, 24 Chassa - 10/09/03; BTA, BNT, bTV - 09/09/03)
